questions: What do you do with broken things?
How important is the colour of a car to you?
What kind of lost things have you found in a public place?
Did you eat a lot of ice cream as a kid?
Have you ever been to a zoo or safari park?
sample_answers:
With broken things, my first response is to see if I can fix it. A lot of things I already know how to fix, and if
not, I will just watch a video online teaching me how to fix it. If I can’t fix it, I will donate it to someone who
can.

The colour of a car is not important to me. I care more about a car’s specifications and features; I enjoy
good quality cars that drive well and are very fast! It does not matter to me what colour the car is.

I often find quite mundane items that people have lost in public places. A common example of lost
items I have found are umbrellas and gloves. People often leave these behind by accident on cold or
rainy days.

I rarely ate ice cream when I was a kid. My parents were very healthy and they thought it was better if children
didn’t eat a lot of sugar. So, we only had ice cream on very special occasions.

Yes, I have been to many zoos and was even lucky enough to once visit a safari park with my parents. There is
a zoo in my home city, and growing up I would visit often. Once, my parents took me to the Guangzhou
Chimelong Safari Park as a reward for doing well in my exams.
